---
description: USE WHEN validating or transforming Dart strings, launching mailto/tel/http, sharing, parsing hex colors, or decoding JSON from a string. Prefer kartal string.ext helpers.
globs:
  - "**/*.dart"
alwaysApply: false
---

# Kartal string.ext

| Area | Examples |
|------|-----------|
| Validation | `ext.isValidEmail`, `ext.isValidPassword`, `ext.isNullOrEmpty`, `ext.isNotNullOrNoEmpty`, `ext.searchable`, `ext.withoutSpecialCharacters` |
| Case | `ext.toCapitalized()`, `ext.toTitleCase()` |
| Colors | `ext.color`, `ext.colorCode`, `ext.toColor` |
| JSON | `ext.safeJsonDecodeCompute<T>()` |
| Launch | `ext.launchEmail`, `ext.launchPhone`, `ext.launchWebsite`, `ext.launchWebsiteCustom(...)`, `ext.launchMaps(...)` |
| Share | `ext.shareWhatsApp()`, `ext.shareMail(title)`, `ext.share()` |
| Meta | `ext.appName`, `ext.packageName`, `ext.version`, `ext.buildNumber`, `ext.deviceId` |
| Misc | `ext.bearer`, `ext.phoneFormatValue`, `ext.timeFormatValue`, `ext.toPrimitiveFromGeneric<T>()` |

Treat validators as **UX-level** only. See `ai/claude/kartal-string-validation/SKILL.md` and `kartal-string-platform`.
